      <notesStmt>
        <note>F. 1r begins with Nivṛttinyāsa (title from ff. 1r and 2r), after which follows Navārṇamantra (title from f. 2r) and its Nyāsa, then Ekādaśanyāsa (title from f. 6r) and a related Dhyāna. The latter half of the manuscript contains a version of Bhūtaśuddhiprāṇapratiṣṭhā (cf. UPenn Ms. Coll. 390, Item 1434 and Item 1380, etc.). Title Bhūtaśuddhyādi from colophon.</note>
        <note>Written 7-8 lines per leaf.</note>
        <note>Two folios (6a and 6b) numbered as f. 6.</note>
        <note>Good condition. Mistakes covered over with yellow or blotched out with black. Marginal corrections.</note>
        <note>Begins, f. 1r: śrīḥ nivṛttinyāsaḥ aṁ nivṛttyai namaḥ śirasi oṁ pratiṣṭhāyai * mukhe iṁ vidyāyai * da * netre * īṁ śāntyai *</note>
        <note>Colophon, f. 2r: iti nivṛttinyāsaḥ</note>
        <note>Colophon, f. 6Ar: iti maṁtramahodadhikārikānusāreṇa ekādaśanyāsaḥ</note>
        <note>Colophon, f. 7r: iti prāṇapratiṣṭhā</note>
        <note>Text ends, f. 9v: akṣasrakkuṁbhavīṇā likhitavarakarāṁ trīkṣaṇāṁ padmasaṁsthāṁm achākalpām atuchastanajaghanabharāṁ bhāratīṁ tāṁ namāmi oṁ catvāri vāk *</note>
        <note>Colophon, f. 9v: iti bahirmātṛkā iti bhūtaśuddhyādi samāptā</note>
      </notesStmt>
